<paragraph id="8B82369AA12CFFBBFA9DFD5AFA21BC82" blockId="13.[192,1440,642,731]" box="[192,1440,642,667]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<keyLead id="30CC95AFA12CFFBBFA9DFD5AFA21BC82" box="[192,1440,642,667]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
1. Elytra completely pubescent, pubescence on disc distinctly visible ........ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D19A12CFFBBFEDDFD5DFA21BC82" authority="(Klug)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[1152,1440,642,667]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Trichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerascens">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFEDDFD5DFA21BC82" bold="true" box="[1152,1440,642,667]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFEDDFD5DFAC2BC82" bold="true" box="[1152,1347,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T. cinerascens</emphasis>
(Klug)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B82369AA12CFFBBFA9DFD7DFA21BCC2" blockId="13.[192,1440,642,731]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<keyLead id="30CC95AFA12CFFBBFA9DFD7DFA21BCC2" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
— Elytra with apical and lateral pubescence, disc not pubescent, or if so pubescence not distinctly visible ........................................................................................................................................ 
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFFCCFD1AFA21BCC2" bold="true" box="[1425,1440,707,731]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C92E3FA12CFFBBFA9DFCDAFA21BD62" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<paragraph id="8B82369AA12CFFBBFA9DFCDAFA21BD22" blockId="13.[192,1440,771,891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<keyLead id="30CC95AFA12CFFBBFA9DFCDAFA21BD22" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
2(1). Ventral surface yellow, if dark then legs pale yellow; elytra pale brownish yellow, with contrasting transverse dark mark on apical declivity of each elytron ...................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D19A12CFFBBFED1FCFDFA21BD22" authority="(Harold)" baseAuthorityName="Harold" box="[1164,1440,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Trichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaumi">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFED1FCFDFA21BD22" bold="true" box="[1164,1440,802,827]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFED1FCFDFAA5BD22" bold="true" box="[1164,1316,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T. schaumi</emphasis>
(Harold)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B82369AA12CFFBBFA9DFC9DFA21BD62" blockId="13.[192,1440,771,891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<keyLead id="30CC95AFA12CFFBBFA9DFC9DFA21BD62" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
— Ventral surface brown or dark brown, legs brown or yellowish brown; elytra brown, with or without obscure transverse mark on apical declivity of each elytron ...................................... 
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFFCCFCBAFA21BD62" bold="true" box="[1425,1440,867,891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">3</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C92E3FA12CFFBBFA9DFC7AFA21BA02" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<paragraph id="8B82369AA12CFFBBFA9DFC7AFA21BDC2" blockId="13.[192,1440,931,1051]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<keyLead id="30CC95AFA12CFFBBFA9DFC7AFA21BDC2" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
3(2). Dorsal color predominantly reddish brown; elytral intervals alutaceous, shiny; body comparatively short, wide ..................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D19A12CFFBBFE17FC1DFA21BDC2" authority="(Boheman)" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[1098,1440,962,987]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Trichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFE17FC1DFA21BDC2" bold="true" box="[1098,1440,962,987]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFE17FC1DFA80BDC2" bold="true" box="[1098,1281,962,987]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T. calcaratus</emphasis>
(Boheman)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B82369AA12CFFBBFA9DFC3DFA21BA02" blockId="13.[192,1440,931,1051]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<keyLead id="30CC95AFA12CFFBBFA9DFC3DFA21BA02" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
— Dorsal color predominantly dark brown; elytral intervals alutaceous, dull; body comparatively elongate, narrow ................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D19A12CFFBBFE29FBDDFA21BA02" authority="(Muller)" baseAuthorityName="Muller" box="[1140,1440,1026,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Trichaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFE29FBDDFA21BA02" bold="true" box="[1140,1440,1026,1051]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B949EA88A12CFFBBFE29FBDDFAA6BA02" bold="true" box="[1140,1319,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T. pulchellus</emphasis>
(Müller)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
